{"lemma":"عُشْرِ","slug":"عُشْرِ","root":"ع.ش.ر","root_slug":"ع-ش-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ش-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عُشْرِ","root":"عشر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","num"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29187","","n29192","n29193","n29194","n29195","n29196"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"masculine of عَشَرَة (ʕašara, “ten”)","tags":["form-of","masculine"]},{"pos":"num","gloss":"-teen (in numerals 11–19, e.g. أَحَدَ عَشَرَ (ʔaḥada ʕašara, “eleven”))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one tenth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"apple of Sodom (Calotropis procera) as well as crown flower (Calotropis gigantea), milkweed (the genus Calotropis, which has only these two species and Calotropis acia in India)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ش ر (ʕ š r); compare عَشَرَة (ʕašara, “ten”).\n\nFrom the root ع ش ر (ʕ š r), perhaps in the sense of association because the fibrous plant yields cordage for medicinal purposes."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29187","headword_ar":"عَشَرَ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", as is expressly stated by the expositors of the Fs and by others, but F, confounding two usages of the verb, says"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took one from ten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arahumo","text_ar":"عَشَرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took one from among them, they being ten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arahumo","text_ar":"عَشَرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) accord. to the K"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is at variance with other authorities, as mentioned above, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, (S, O,) the former correct, but the latter is preferred by MF, who quotes it from the Expositions of the Fs, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$uwrN","text_ar":"عُشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$~rhumo","text_ar":"عشّرهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEo$iyrN","text_ar":"تَعْشِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took from them the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$or","text_ar":"عُشْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, by extension of the term in the Muslim law, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half of the tenth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quarter of the tenth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their several kinds of property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) And in like manner you say, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$ara AlmaAla","text_ar":"عَشَرَ المَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$uwrN","text_ar":"عُشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$~rhu","text_ar":"عشّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$or","text_ar":"عُشْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) It is said in a trad., respecting women,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yuEo$arona","text_ar":"لَا يُعْشَرْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They shall not have the tenth of the value of their ornaments taken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$ara","text_ar":"عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He added one to nine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) [In the TA and CK, this signification is connected with the first mentioned above, at the commencement of this art., by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo","text_ar":"اَوْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is evidently the right reading.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arahumo","text_ar":"عَشَرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$orN","text_ar":"عَشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became the tenth of them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made them ten by"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adding to their number"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also 2: and see Q. Q. 1.]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","O","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n29192","headword_ar":"عَشْرٌ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$arapN","text_ar":"عَشَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n29193","headword_ar":"عُشْرٌ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$urN","text_ar":"عُشُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tenth; a tenth part; one part of ten parts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrN","text_ar":"عَشِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEo$aArN","text_ar":"مِعْشَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) which last is [of a form] not used [to denote a fractional part] except as applied to the tenth part (S, O) and [in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirobaAEN","text_ar":"مِرْبَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to] the fourth part: (O:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEo$aArN","text_ar":"مِعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth of the tenth"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hundredth part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEo$aArN","text_ar":"مِعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyr","text_ar":"عَشِير","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$or","text_ar":"عُشْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that, accord. to this, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mE$Ar","text_ar":"معشار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of a thousand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth of the tenth of the tenth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [in the TA, “ and as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mE$Ar","text_ar":"معشار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$yr","text_ar":"عشير"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” but this is evidently a mistake:] the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$uwrN","text_ar":"عُشُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and that of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrN","text_ar":"عَشِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$iraA='u","text_ar":"اَعْشِرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, Msb:) it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tisoEapu A^aEo$iraA='i Alr~izoqi fiY Alt~ijaArapi wajuzo'N minohaA","text_ar":"تِسْعَةُ اَعْشِرَا=ءِ الرِّزْقِ فِى التِّجَارَةِ وَجُزْءٌ مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Als~aAbiyaA='i","text_ar":"فِى السَّابِيَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nine tenths of the means of subsistence consist in merchandise, and one part of them consists in"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the increase of animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * O. *) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a Eu$ora A^amowaAlihimo","text_ar":"اَخَذَ عُشْرَ اَمْوَالِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took the tenth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tithe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or by extension of the term in the Muslim law,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the half of the tenth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the quarter of the tenth, of their several kinds of property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) [See 1, and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$~aArN","text_ar":"عَشَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as a pl. of which the sing. is not mentioned], applied to she-camels,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That excern into the udder"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tunozilu","text_ar":"تُنْزِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a scanty"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dir~ap","text_ar":"دِرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity of milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dar~ap","text_ar":"دَرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without its collecting"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and increasing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n29194","headword_ar":"عِشْرٌ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A period of eight days between"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels'"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice coming to water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for they come to water on the tenth day [counting the day of the next preceding watering as the first]; and in like manner, the term for every one of the periods between two waterings is with kesr: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vilovN","text_ar":"ثِلْثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels' coming to water on the tenth day"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the next preceding period of abstinence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counting the day of the next preceding watering as the first"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the ninth day"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not counting the day of the next preceding watering;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for it is evident that these two explanations are virtually one and the the same]; (K;) as in the Shems el-'Uloom, on the authority of Kh, where it is added that they keep them from the water nine nights and eight days, and then bring them to water on the ninth day, which is the tenth from [by which is meant including] the former [day of] watering: (TA:) after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$or","text_ar":"عِشْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", there is no name for a period between the two waterings until the twentieth [day]; (S, O;) but you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiYa taridu Ei$orFA wagib~FA","text_ar":"هِىَ تَرِدُ عِشْرًا وَغِبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orFA wariboEFA","text_ar":"عِشْرًا وَرِبْعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and so on,] to the twentieth [day counting the day of the next preceding watering as the first]; (As;) and then you say, that their period between two waterings is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oraAni","text_ar":"عِشْرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, O,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eighteen days;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;) and when they exceed this, they are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAziy^u","text_ar":"جَوَازِيُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning “ that satisfy themselves with green pasture so as not to need water ”]. (As, S, O.) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eighth young one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece that is broken off"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a cooking-pot, (K, TA,) or from a drinking-cup or bowl, (TA,) and from anything; (K, TA;) as though it were one of ten pieces; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$aArapN","text_ar":"عُشَارَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (O, TA:) pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaA$iyru","text_ar":"اَعَاشِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) and of ↓ the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$aAraAtN","text_ar":"عُشَارَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buromapN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"بُرْمَةٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cookingpot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of stone, broken in pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus [we find the latter word] occurring in the pl. form [and used as an epithet]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qidorN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"قِدْرٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cooking-pot broken into ten pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large cooking-pot, of ten pieces joined together by reason of its largeness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cooking-pot so large that it is carried by ten men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by ten women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cooking-pot broken in pieces;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not derived from anything: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quduwrN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"قُدُورٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEaA$iyru","text_ar":"اَعَاشِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jafonN","text_ar":"جَفْنٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A scabbard of a sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sword-case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken in pieces."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobN A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"قَلْبٌ اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A broken heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aAru jazuwrK","text_ar":"اَعْشَارُ جَزُورٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The portions of a slaughtered camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for which players at the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"contend, and which are ten in number; not seven, as is said in one place in the TA. In Har p. 579,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AE$Ar","text_ar":"اعشار"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case is said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but I think that we have better reason for regarding it as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$orN","text_ar":"عِشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Az, S, O, K.) Imra-el-Keys says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA *arafato EayonaAki A_il~aA litaDoribiY\n                      \n                     \n                        bisahomayoki fiY A^aEo$aAri qalobK muqat~ali"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And thine eyes did not shed tears but that thou mightest play with thy two arrows for the portions of a heart subdued and killed by the passion of love"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he means, by the two arrows, the two called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEal~aY","text_ar":"المُعَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aqiyb","text_ar":"الرَّقِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; to the former of which are assigned seven portions, and to the latter, three; so that both together gain all the portions; for the slaughtered camel is divided into ten portions: therefore he means that she has played for his heart with her two arrows, [alluding to the glances shot from her eyes,] and gained possession of it altogether: (Az, S, * O: * [see also a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybN","text_ar":"رَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or accord. to some, he means that his heart had been broken, and then repaired like as cooking-pots are repaired: but Az says that the former explanation, which is mentioned by Th, pleases him more. (TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba fiY A^aEo$aArihi walamo yaroDa bimiEo$aArihi","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ فِى اَعْشَارِهِ وَلَمْ يَرْضَ بِمِعْشَارِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He played for"},{"kind":"text","text":"all"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the portions of it, and was not content with the fifth of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning he took the whole of it. (A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cooking-pots that boil the ten portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwr","text_ar":"جَزُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har. p. 579.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEo$aArN","text_ar":"اَعْشَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"primary feathers of the wing of a bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaA$iru","text_ar":"عَوَاشِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","As","K","A"]},{"entry_id":"n29195","headword_ar":"عُشَرٌ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Three nights of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lunar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"month,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tenth, eleventh, and twelfth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tusaE","text_ar":"تُسَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, O.)       -A2-  Also [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asclepias gigantea"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linnæus; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gigantic swallow-wort;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrub"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is a substance answering the purpose of tinder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like cotton,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"than which there is nothing better wherein to strike fire, and with which cushions are stuffed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on account of its softness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA='N","text_ar":"رَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwA^","text_ar":"روا"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to AHn, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large species of tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrub"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a sweet gum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, O, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and milk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and broad leaves, growing up high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the flowers and shoots of which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the joints of the branches and from the places of the flowers whereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there comes forth a well-known kind of sugar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, O, * K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is somewhat of bitterness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~aru AlEu$ari","text_ar":"سُكَّرُ العُشَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHn, TA;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is a kind of red sugar, which falls like dew upon this tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Golius, from Ibn-Maaroof and the Mj;)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it produces also bladders, resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaA$iq","text_ar":"شَقَاشِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faucial bags"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels, in which they bray,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[blowing them out from their months, with a gurgling sound,] (AHn, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the bladder of the smaller"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qataAd","text_ar":"قَتَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it has a blossom like that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"difolaY","text_ar":"دِفْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tinged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but with what hue is not said,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and shining, and beautiful in appearance, as well as a fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and pl. [of this"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2052},{"kind":"text","text":"latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$arN","text_ar":"عُشَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather this is a coll. gen. n.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$araAtN","text_ar":"عُشَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaEN","text_ar":"سَلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n29196","headword_ar":"عُشُرٌ","root":"E$r","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}